hopobject.body: I'm sorry, I didn't catch your name pharmacie galerie lafayette limoges As for Palace's defenders, the majority lack Premier League experience and those that have it are rather short on pace. Joel Ward (£2.4m) and Jonny Parr (£2.5m) are both solid full-backs who offer plenty going forward, however, with the Eagles’ goalmouth certain to be tested regularly this season, none of Palace’s backline are likely to be regular point scorers. Goalkeeper Julian Speroni (£3.0) could be a busy man in the Palace goal and clean sheets will probably be a rarity, especially as manager Ian Holloway’s teams are traditionally better known for their aggressive brand of attacking football, rather than their defensive capabilities. Back in 2010-11, Holloway’s Blackpool side conceded 78 goals and whilst Palace scored 73 goals in the Championship last year, they also let in 63.
